snippet.textDisplay:
What I still don't understand is why they decided to use the Archie comic. Like, it was a good, wholesome comic strip way back when. I grew up on it. The only way it and this objectively terrible show are even tangentially related are the character names and the smallest of similarities in their physical description. Oh, and the towns called Riverdale.

Archie is a normal guy, bit of a jock, but otherwise an ok guy and the center character.

Jughead's a bottomless pit with a great metabolism and doesn't care about much other than food.

Betty is the wholesome girl next door and one of Archie's two love interests.

Veronica is the other half Archie's heart, and is the rich girl of town, kinda selfish, but still a decent person.

Who the hell are these people?!?
